1
00:00:06,866 --> 00:00:09,200
[ BIRDS TWITTERING ]

2
00:00:11,900 --> 00:00:15,333
THEY'RE ANNOUNCING
OUR TEST SCORES TODAY.

3
00:00:15,366 --> 00:00:18,400
OH, BY THE WAY,
HAVE YOU MADE
ANY NEW FRIENDS YET?

4
00:00:20,466 --> 00:00:21,866
MM-HMM.

5
00:00:21,900 --> 00:00:23,500
I'D BETTER GET GOING.

6
00:00:23,533 --> 00:00:24,766
HAVE A GOOD DAY.

7
00:00:33,866 --> 00:00:36,566
[ SIGHS ]
HAVE I MADE FRIENDS?

8
00:00:36,600 --> 00:00:39,366
[ SUGURO ]
SHE'S YOUR GIRLFRIEND,
ISN'T SHE?

9
00:00:39,400 --> 00:00:42,200
YOU GOT THE WRONG IDEA
ABOUT US, MAN.

10
00:00:42,233 --> 00:00:44,800
SO WHAT ARE YOU SAYING?
YOU GUYS JUST FRIENDS, HUH?

11
00:00:44,833 --> 00:00:48,066
WHAT? ARE YOU KIDDING ME?
NO.

12
00:00:48,100 --> 00:00:50,133
[ WHIMPERS ]

13
00:00:50,166 --> 00:00:52,833
DON'T CRY, SHIEMI.
THERE'S NO TIME...

14
00:00:52,866 --> 00:00:54,933
'CAUSE TODAY'S THE DAY.

15
00:00:54,966 --> 00:00:57,600
I'M GONNA GO OUT
AND MAKE SOME NEW FRIENDS.

16
00:01:08,800 --> 00:01:11,166
MISS KAMIKI, MISS PAKU.

17
00:01:11,200 --> 00:01:12,833
HELLO. I WAS WONDERING--

18
00:01:12,866 --> 00:01:15,333
[ SHRIEKS ]

19
00:01:15,366 --> 00:01:17,666
OW. THAT HURT.

20
00:01:17,700 --> 00:01:19,966
MISS MORIYAMA?

21
00:01:20,000 --> 00:01:22,300
YOU KLUTZ.

22
00:01:22,333 --> 00:01:24,066
[ WHIMPERS ]

23
00:01:24,100 --> 00:01:27,033
ARE YOU OKAY?
MM-HMM.

24
00:01:27,066 --> 00:01:30,366
TRY TO BE MORE CAREFUL.
WAIT UP, IZUMO.

25
00:01:32,000 --> 00:01:34,300
[ RIN ]
SHIEMI?

26
00:01:34,333 --> 00:01:37,066
EVERYTHING OKAY?
WHAT YOU DOING DOWN THERE?

27
00:01:37,100 --> 00:01:40,366
UM, NOTHING.
I'M FINE.

28
00:01:42,466 --> 00:01:46,466
I CAN'T DEPEND ON RIN.
I'VE GOT TO DO THIS ON MY OWN.

29
00:01:56,933 --> 00:02:00,166
♪ [ MAN SINGING
IN JAPANESE ]

30
00:03:20,538 --> 00:03:22,105
LISTEN UP.

31
00:03:22,138 --> 00:03:24,972
SUMMER VACATION
IS LESS THAN A MONTH
AND A HALF AWAY,

32
00:03:25,005 --> 00:03:26,938
BUT BEFORE THE BREAK,
YOU'RE GOING TO BE TAKING...

33
00:03:26,972 --> 00:03:29,238
THIS YEAR'S
EXWIRE AUTHORIZATION EXAM.

34
00:03:29,272 --> 00:03:31,972
ESQUIRE EXAM?
WHAT THE HECK'S THAT?

35
00:03:32,005 --> 00:03:34,572
NO, EXWIRE.
HUH?

36
00:03:34,605 --> 00:03:37,038
A CANDIDATE FOR BECOMING
AN EXORCIST.

37
00:03:37,072 --> 00:03:38,072
HUH.

38
00:03:38,105 --> 00:03:39,905
I WANT EVERYONE
TO KEEP IN MIND...

39
00:03:39,938 --> 00:03:41,438
THAT ONCE YOU'RE PROMOTED
TO EXWIRE...

40
00:03:41,472 --> 00:03:44,405
YOU'LL BE SUBJECTED
TO MORE SPECIALIZED
COMBAT TRAINING.

41
00:03:44,438 --> 00:03:48,705
THE EXAM WON'T BE EASY TO PASS,
THEREFORE, STARTING MONDAY,

42
00:03:48,738 --> 00:03:51,872
WE'RE OFFERING
A WEEKLONG BOOT CAMP
TO PREPARE YOU FOR THE EXAM.

43
00:03:51,905 --> 00:03:53,338
A BOOT CAMP?

44
00:03:53,372 --> 00:03:56,405
SINCE ATTENDING THE CAMP
ISN'T MANDATORY,

45
00:03:56,438 --> 00:03:59,505
INDICATE WHETHER OR NOT
YOU'LL BE PARTICIPATING
ON THE FORM.

46
00:03:59,538 --> 00:04:03,572
IF YOU ARE, PLEASE INDICATE
THE MEISTER, OR TITLE,
THAT YOU'D LIKE TO ACQUIRE,

47
00:04:03,605 --> 00:04:05,438
AND TURN THE FORM IN BY MONDAY.

48
00:04:05,472 --> 00:04:08,105
A MEISTER OR A TITLE?

49
00:04:08,138 --> 00:04:11,705
HEY, COULD YOU TELL ME
WHAT A MEISTER IS?

50
00:04:11,738 --> 00:04:13,038
HUH?

51
00:04:13,072 --> 00:04:17,472
UH, COME ON.
HELP ME OUT HERE.
PLEASE.

52
00:04:17,505 --> 00:04:20,972
GIVE ME A BREAK.
YOU WANT TO BE AN EXORCIST,
BUT YOU DON'T KNOW WHAT THAT IS?

53
00:04:21,005 --> 00:04:22,538
SERIOUSLY,
WHAT'S WITH YOU?

54
00:04:22,572 --> 00:04:24,872
[ CHUCKLES ]
YOU REALLY ARE
TOTALLY CLUELESS,

55
00:04:24,905 --> 00:04:27,872
- AREN'T YOU, OKUMURA?
- FINE. I DON'T HAVE A CLUE.

56
00:04:27,905 --> 00:04:30,038
SO ARE YOU GONNA TELL ME
OR WHAT?

57
00:04:30,072 --> 00:04:32,805
I'LL TELL YOU.
IT'S A TECHNICAL
QUALIFICATION...

58
00:04:32,838 --> 00:04:34,772
THAT'S REQUIRED
TO BECOME AN EXORCIST.

59
00:04:34,805 --> 00:04:39,505
IT'S A TITLE GIVEN TO THOSE
WHO'VE PROVED THEY'VE GOT
GREAT SKILLS.

60
00:04:39,538 --> 00:04:41,338
THERE ARE FIVE MEISTERS IN ALL.

61
00:04:41,372 --> 00:04:46,038
KNIGHT, DRAGOON, TAMER,
ARIA AND DOCTOR.

62
00:04:46,072 --> 00:04:50,038
AS LONG AS YOU'VE ACQUIRED
AT LEAST ONE OF THOSE,
YOU CAN BECOME AN EXORCIST.

63
00:04:50,072 --> 00:04:52,738
OH, OKAY.
I THINK I GET IT NOW.

64
00:04:52,772 --> 00:04:54,505
NO ONE SAID
YOU COULD SIT WITH US.

65
00:04:54,538 --> 00:04:57,272
THE OTHER THING IS,
YOUR STYLE OF COMBAT
WILL DIFFER...

66
00:04:57,305 --> 00:04:59,105
DEPENDING ON WHICH MEISTER
YOU ARE.

67
00:04:59,138 --> 00:05:01,938
SWEET. THANKS FOR EXPLAINING,
KONEKOMARU.

68
00:05:01,972 --> 00:05:03,938
WHICH ONE ARE YOU GOING FOR?

69
00:05:03,972 --> 00:05:06,572
WELL, SHIMA AND I
ARE GOING TO TRY
FOR ARIA.

70
00:05:06,605 --> 00:05:08,238
HMM? ARIA?

71
00:05:08,272 --> 00:05:10,438
ARIA'S A MEISTER
THAT BATTLES DEMONS...

72
00:05:10,472 --> 00:05:14,005
BY RECITING PASSAGES
FROM THE BIBLE
AND OTHER SACRED SCRIPTURES.

73
00:05:14,038 --> 00:05:16,738
BON HERE'S GONNA GO
FOR BOTH ARIA AND DRAGOON...

74
00:05:16,772 --> 00:05:18,705
'CAUSE HE'S ALL HARD CORE
AND EVERYTHING.

75
00:05:18,738 --> 00:05:20,705
WOW. THAT'S OUR BON.

76
00:05:20,738 --> 00:05:22,405
DO NOT CALL ME BON!

77
00:05:22,438 --> 00:05:26,038
ACTUALLY, OUR INSTRUCTOR,
MR. OKUMURA, HAS TWO MEISTERS--

78
00:05:26,072 --> 00:05:27,538
DOCTOR AND DRAGOON.

79
00:05:27,572 --> 00:05:29,372
HUH. YUKIO KICKS BUTT.

80
00:05:29,405 --> 00:05:33,072
HMM. I WONDER WHICH OF THOSE
I SHOULD GO FOR.

81
00:05:33,105 --> 00:05:35,072
THIS DRAGOON-- WHAT IS IT?

82
00:05:35,105 --> 00:05:36,505
[ LOUD THUMP ]
HUH?

83
00:05:36,538 --> 00:05:39,038
MY GOD!
YOU ARE SUCH A PAIN.

84
00:05:39,072 --> 00:05:42,072
A DRAGOON'S A MEISTER
WHO FIGHTS WITH FIREARMS.

85
00:05:42,105 --> 00:05:44,938
AND A KNIGHT'S
A MEISTER WHO FIGHTS
WITH A FRIGGIN' SWORD.

86
00:05:44,972 --> 00:05:47,705
[ SHIMA CHUCKLES ]
SEE? EVEN WITH
ALL THE GRUMBLING,

87
00:05:47,738 --> 00:05:49,472
BON CAN STILL BE HELPFUL.

88
00:05:49,505 --> 00:05:50,838
[ SUGURO ]
SHUT UP!

89
00:05:50,872 --> 00:05:53,338
- BACK UP.
YOU SAY SWORD?
- MM-HMM.

90
00:05:53,372 --> 00:05:56,305
THE MEISTERS WHO SPECIALIZE
IN SWORD FIGHTING
ARE CALLED KNIGHTS.

91
00:05:56,338 --> 00:05:58,038
OKAY. THEN I'M GONNA BE
A KNIGHT.

92
00:05:58,072 --> 00:06:00,905
YEAH, YOU KNOW, I ALWAYS SEE YOU
CARRYING THAT SWORD AROUND.

93
00:06:00,938 --> 00:06:03,938
YEP. IT'S SORT OF LIKE
A KEEPSAKE FROM MY DAD.

94
00:06:03,972 --> 00:06:07,905
RIN SEEMS LIKE HE'S HAPPIER
WHEN HE'S HANGING OUT
WITH THE OTHER BOYS.

95
00:06:07,938 --> 00:06:10,972
I'VE GOT TO BE STRONG THOUGH.
BUT WHAT SHOULD I DO?

96
00:06:11,005 --> 00:06:13,105
RIN AND YUKI
HELPED ME GET IN HERE.

97
00:06:13,138 --> 00:06:16,272
NO. IT'S NOT THEIR JOB
TO TAKE CARE OF ME.

98
00:06:16,305 --> 00:06:17,905
IT'S MINE.

99
00:06:23,162 --> 00:06:26,762
ALL RIGHT.
I WILL NOW SUMMON A DEMON.

100
00:06:26,796 --> 00:06:28,762
- WHOA.
- WATCH YOUR STEP.

101
00:06:28,796 --> 00:06:32,296
IF THE MAGIC CIRCLE IS BROKEN,
IT WILL LOSE ITS EFFECT.

102
00:06:32,329 --> 00:06:35,529
NOW, TO SUMMON A DEMON,
YOU'LL NEED
A DROP OF YOUR BLOOD...

103
00:06:35,562 --> 00:06:37,729
AND A SUITABLE INVOCATION.

104
00:06:39,562 --> 00:06:42,829
SON OF TYPHOEUS AND ECHIDNA,

105
00:06:42,862 --> 00:06:45,429
HEAR MY CALL AND SHOW YOURSELF.

106
00:06:45,462 --> 00:06:47,196
[ GASPING ]

107
00:06:54,096 --> 00:06:56,962
[ LOW GROANING ]

108
00:06:56,996 --> 00:06:58,962
IS THAT A NABERIUS?

109
00:06:58,996 --> 00:07:01,796
I'VE NEVER SEEN ONE.
EW, SULFUR.

110
00:07:01,829 --> 00:07:05,596
SUMMONING A DEMON
TO USE AS A FAMILIAR
IS A RARE TRAIT.

111
00:07:05,629 --> 00:07:07,429
NOT EVERYONE IS CAPABLE.

112
00:07:07,462 --> 00:07:11,262
NOW, TO TAME A DEMON,
YOU MUST HAVE A STRONG WILL
AND UNSHAKABLE NERVE.

113
00:07:11,296 --> 00:07:14,529
HAVING A NATURAL TALENT FOR IT
IS ALSO VALUABLE.

114
00:07:14,562 --> 00:07:15,862
HUH?

115
00:07:15,896 --> 00:07:17,362
TODAY I'M GOING TO TEST YOU...

116
00:07:17,396 --> 00:07:19,529
TO SEE IF ANYONE HERE
HAS THIS TALENT.

117
00:07:19,562 --> 00:07:22,162
- A TEST?
- AT THE BEGINNING OF CLASS,

118
00:07:22,196 --> 00:07:25,396
I HANDED OUT PIECES OF PAPER
WITH A COPY OF THE MAGIC CIRCLE.

119
00:07:25,429 --> 00:07:28,696
PLACE A DROP OF BLOOD ON IT
AND CHANT WHATEVER WORDS
MAY COME TO MIND.

120
00:07:32,262 --> 00:07:35,562
I HUMBLY APPEAL TO THEE,
OH GODDESS INARI.

121
00:07:35,596 --> 00:07:39,462
GRANT MY REQUEST.
LEAVE NOT MY PRAYERS TO THEE
UNFULFILLED.

122
00:07:46,229 --> 00:07:49,629
WHOA! THAT'S SO
UNBELIEVABLY COOL.

123
00:07:49,662 --> 00:07:52,996
A PAIR OF WHITE FOXES.
NICELY DONE, MISS KAMIKI.

124
00:07:53,029 --> 00:07:55,196
IZUMO, THAT'S AMAZING.

125
00:07:55,229 --> 00:07:57,262
I TRIED,
BUT I DIDN'T GET ANYTHING.

126
00:07:57,296 --> 00:08:00,229
THAT FIGURES.
I COME FROM A LONG LINE
OF SHRINE MAIDENS.

127
00:08:00,262 --> 00:08:02,129
THIS ISN'T WORKING.
I CAN'T DO IT.

128
00:08:02,162 --> 00:08:04,996
ME NEITHER.
HMM.

129
00:08:06,862 --> 00:08:09,262
MISS KAMIKI'S AMAZING.

130
00:08:09,296 --> 00:08:10,696
HERE GOES.

131
00:08:10,729 --> 00:08:13,462
UM, I'D LIKE TO TRY IT NEXT.

132
00:08:14,796 --> 00:08:17,462
COME ON, BOY.
COME ON, BOY.

133
00:08:17,496 --> 00:08:19,029
OR SOMETHING.

134
00:08:21,696 --> 00:08:23,429
HMM.

135
00:08:26,629 --> 00:08:27,596
NEE!

136
00:08:32,596 --> 00:08:35,162
NEE!

137
00:08:35,196 --> 00:08:38,896
IF I'M NOT MISTAKEN,
THAT LOOKS LIKE A BABY GREENMAN.

138
00:08:38,929 --> 00:08:41,296
EXCELLENT, MISS MORIYAMA.
EXCELLENT.

139
00:08:41,329 --> 00:08:42,696
[ HUFFS ]

140
00:08:42,729 --> 00:08:44,529
N-NICE TO MEET YOU.

141
00:08:44,562 --> 00:08:46,429
NEE! NEE.

142
00:08:46,462 --> 00:08:48,462
[ GIGGLES ]

143
00:08:49,929 --> 00:08:52,062
THIS IS MY CHANCE
TO TALK TO HER.

144
00:08:52,096 --> 00:08:54,129
UM, HEY, MISS KAMIKI?

145
00:08:54,162 --> 00:08:57,562
I-I SUMMONED
MY FAMILIAR TOO.

146
00:08:57,596 --> 00:09:02,162
ADORABLE. IT'S LIKE
SO UNBELIEVABLY TINY...

147
00:09:02,196 --> 00:09:04,962
AND RIDICULOUSLY CUTE,
LIKE A PEANUT.

148
00:09:04,996 --> 00:09:06,829
HUH? REALLY?

149
00:09:06,862 --> 00:09:09,729
YOU THINK HE'S CUTE?
OH, THANK YOU.

150
00:09:09,762 --> 00:09:12,829
LOOKS AS THOUGH WE HAVE
OUR TAMER CANDIDATES
FOR THIS CLASS.

151
00:09:12,862 --> 00:09:16,462
NOW THEN, TAMERS
ARE VALUABLE IN COMBAT.

152
00:09:16,496 --> 00:09:20,362
THE ABILITY TO CONTROL DEMONS
IS EXTREMELY RARE
AMONG EXORCISTS.

153
00:09:20,396 --> 00:09:24,262
A DEMON WILL NOT OBEY
IF IT PERCEIVES ITS MASTER
TO BE WEAK.

154
00:09:24,296 --> 00:09:27,829
IF ITS MASTER LACKS WILLPOWER,
THE DEMON WILL ATTACK THEM.

155
00:09:27,862 --> 00:09:29,196
OH.

156
00:09:31,862 --> 00:09:33,562
NEE!

157
00:09:33,596 --> 00:09:35,329
WE'RE OKAY, RIGHT?

158
00:09:35,362 --> 00:09:38,262
AS I MENTIONED EARLIER,
ONCE YOU BREAK THE CIRCLE,

159
00:09:38,296 --> 00:09:41,362
YOU RELEASE THE FAMILIAR
FROM YOUR CONTROL
AND IT VANISHES.

160
00:09:41,396 --> 00:09:46,029
SO IF YOU EVER FEEL
LIKE YOU'RE IN DANGER,
SIMPLY TEAR UP THE PAPER.

161
00:09:46,062 --> 00:09:47,896
[ ALL GASP ]
[ CLOCK CHIMES ]

162
00:09:47,929 --> 00:09:51,862
THAT'S ALL FOR TODAY.
CLASS DISMISSED.

163
00:09:51,896 --> 00:09:53,296
NEE?

164
00:09:55,096 --> 00:09:57,629
I WON'T MAKE YOU DISAPPEAR,
I PROMISE.

165
00:09:57,662 --> 00:09:59,796
IS IT OKAY
IF I CALL YOU NEE?

166
00:09:59,829 --> 00:10:00,729
NEE.

167
00:10:01,929 --> 00:10:04,162
LET'S GET OUT OF HERE.
UH, S-SURE.

168
00:10:10,529 --> 00:10:11,996
HEY, MISS KAMIKI?

169
00:10:12,029 --> 00:10:14,996
UM--
IZUMO, SHE'S CALLING YOU.

170
00:10:15,029 --> 00:10:17,762
IGNORE HER, PAKU.
KEEP WALKING.

171
00:10:17,796 --> 00:10:20,162
THAT GIRL'S SO ANNOYING.

172
00:10:20,196 --> 00:10:22,962
[ SHIEMI ]
WAIT UP!
WAIT!

173
00:10:22,996 --> 00:10:25,996
WAIT! WAIT!

174
00:10:26,029 --> 00:10:29,462
WAIT! WAIT!

175
00:10:29,496 --> 00:10:30,696
WAIT!

176
00:10:30,729 --> 00:10:32,029
[ GROWLS ]

177
00:10:32,062 --> 00:10:34,229
WHY ARE YOU FOLLOWING ME AROUND?

178
00:10:34,262 --> 00:10:36,796
OKAY, YOU SUMMONED A FAMILIAR.
BIG DEAL.

179
00:10:36,829 --> 00:10:38,496
DO YOU THINK
THAT MAKES YOU SPECIAL NOW?

180
00:10:38,529 --> 00:10:40,029
HUH?

181
00:10:40,896 --> 00:10:43,829
UM, I JUST--

182
00:10:43,862 --> 00:10:46,396
UM, I, UH--
I'D LIKE...

183
00:10:46,429 --> 00:10:48,929
TO-- TO--

184
00:10:48,962 --> 00:10:51,296
WOULD YOU PLEASE
BE MY FRIEND?

185
00:10:51,329 --> 00:10:52,562
OH.

186
00:10:53,796 --> 00:10:55,096
HUH?

187
00:10:55,129 --> 00:10:57,329
YOU SEE, I, UH,

188
00:10:57,362 --> 00:11:01,229
I'VE NEVER HAD
ANY FRIENDS BEFORE.

189
00:11:01,262 --> 00:11:03,929
SO, UM--

190
00:11:03,962 --> 00:11:05,696
HMM.

191
00:11:05,729 --> 00:11:08,196
- ALL RIGHT THEN.
- HUH?

192
00:11:08,229 --> 00:11:11,029
I SAID ALL RIGHT.
WE'LL BE FRIENDS FROM NOW ON.

193
00:11:11,062 --> 00:11:14,162
REALLY?
[ CHUCKLES ]

194
00:11:14,196 --> 00:11:18,962
- I'M SO HAPPY.
- GOOD. HANG ON TO THIS
FOR ME, OKAY?

195
00:11:18,996 --> 00:11:22,562
I GET TIRED EASY
'CAUSE I'M NOT THAT STRONG.

196
00:11:22,596 --> 00:11:25,662
AFTER ALL, FRIENDS ARE SUPPOSED
TO HELP EACH OTHER OUT.

197
00:11:25,696 --> 00:11:27,862
THAT'S WHAT FRIENDS ARE FOR,
RIGHT?

198
00:11:27,896 --> 00:11:30,362
FRIENDS HELP EACH OTHER.

199
00:11:31,562 --> 00:11:33,062
[ GIGGLES ]

200
00:11:36,429 --> 00:11:38,929
IZUMO, ARE YOU SURE
ABOUT THIS?

201
00:11:38,962 --> 00:11:41,529
SHE SEEMS HAPPY ENOUGH,
SO WHAT'S THE PROBLEM?

202
00:11:42,696 --> 00:11:44,029
HUH?

203
00:11:44,062 --> 00:11:45,862
WHAT'S UP WITH THAT?

204
00:11:45,896 --> 00:11:49,629
SHIEMI'S CARRYING
POLKA BROW'S STUFF LIKE
SHE'S HER MAID OR SOMETHING.

205
00:11:49,662 --> 00:11:50,996
POLKA BROW?

206
00:11:51,029 --> 00:11:52,796
[ LAUGHS ]
HE MEANS MISS KAMIKI.

207
00:11:52,829 --> 00:11:55,262
[ SUGURO ]
THEY'RE JUST MESSING AROUND.

208
00:12:07,377 --> 00:12:10,077
HERE. PASS THESE OUT
FOR ME, WILL YOU?

209
00:12:10,110 --> 00:12:11,810
UH-HUH.

210
00:12:11,843 --> 00:12:14,910
WE'RE USING VALERIANA
IN OUR NEXT PHARMACEUTICS CLASS.

211
00:12:14,943 --> 00:12:16,243
MAKE SURE AND GET ME SOME, OKAY?

212
00:12:16,277 --> 00:12:18,110
UH-HUH.

213
00:12:18,143 --> 00:12:20,577
MELON BREAD AND FRUIT MILK.
GOT IT?

214
00:12:20,610 --> 00:12:21,877
UH-HUH.

215
00:12:24,110 --> 00:12:25,710
UNBELIEVABLE.

216
00:12:25,743 --> 00:12:29,810
POOR SHIEMI.
SHE'S RUNNING AROUND
LIKE AN ERRAND GIRL.

217
00:12:29,843 --> 00:12:31,110
WHAT?
YEAH.

218
00:12:31,143 --> 00:12:35,177
NOTHING. SO WHY ARE WE HAVING
BOOT CAMP IN OUR DORM ANYWAY?

219
00:12:35,210 --> 00:12:38,143
IT'S CONVENIENT,
AND BESIDES, WE'RE
THE ONLY ONES LIVING HERE...

220
00:12:38,177 --> 00:12:40,010
SO WE WON'T
BE DISTURBING ANYONE.

221
00:12:40,043 --> 00:12:42,210
IT'S GOING TO BE FINE.
HUH?

222
00:12:42,243 --> 00:12:44,977
GOOD MORNING.
YOUR CLASS HAS ARRIVED.

223
00:12:45,010 --> 00:12:46,577
[ YUKIO ]
GOOD MORNING, EVERYONE.

224
00:12:46,610 --> 00:12:52,343
SERIOUSLY? THIS THING
LOOKS LIKE SOMETHING
OUT OF A HORROR MOVIE.

225
00:12:52,377 --> 00:12:55,543
WOW, IT'S SO CREEPY.
AND UGLY.

226
00:12:55,577 --> 00:12:58,043
WAS THIS THE BEST PLACE
WE COULD FIND TO DO THIS?

227
00:12:58,077 --> 00:13:01,110
OH. TAKE IT.
UH-HUH.

228
00:13:01,143 --> 00:13:02,643
[ GROWLS ]

229
00:13:02,677 --> 00:13:06,210
MISS MORIYAMA,
IF YOU DON'T WANT TO,
JUST SAY SO.

230
00:13:06,243 --> 00:13:08,777
HUH? OH, NO,
I DON'T MIND AT ALL.

231
00:13:08,810 --> 00:13:11,677
I'M JUST HELPING OUT A FRIEND
BECAUSE THAT'S
WHAT FRIENDS ARE FOR.

232
00:13:11,710 --> 00:13:13,610
UH, OKAY.

233
00:13:14,710 --> 00:13:15,943
TIME'S UP.

234
00:13:15,977 --> 00:13:18,510
TURN YOUR PAPERS OVER
AND HAND THEM IN, PLEASE.

235
00:13:18,543 --> 00:13:21,510
[ ALL GRUMBLING ]
WHEW. THANK GOD
IT'S OVER.

236
00:13:21,543 --> 00:13:23,110
THAT TOOK
FOREVER.

237
00:13:23,143 --> 00:13:26,010
I'M GONNA GO GET
SOME AIR. LATER.

238
00:13:26,043 --> 00:13:27,510
YEAH, GOOD IDEA.

239
00:13:27,543 --> 00:13:30,243
I WANT EVERYONE UP
BY 6:00 A.M. TOMORROW.

240
00:13:30,277 --> 00:13:32,243
THAT'LL GIVE US AN HOUR
BEFORE WE START CLASS...

241
00:13:32,277 --> 00:13:34,077
TO GO OVER THE ANSWERS
TO THE TEST.

242
00:13:34,110 --> 00:13:35,910
[ GROANS ]

243
00:13:35,943 --> 00:13:37,510
DEMON. SADIST.

244
00:13:37,543 --> 00:13:39,843
PAKU, LET'S GO TAKE A BATH.

245
00:13:39,877 --> 00:13:42,243
MM-HMM.
OH, I WANNA GO.

246
00:13:42,277 --> 00:13:44,443
[ PAKU ]
I HOPE THE BATHTUB'S BIG.

247
00:13:44,477 --> 00:13:46,943
[ KAMIKI ]
I DON'T CARE.
I JUST WANNA SOAK.

248
00:13:46,977 --> 00:13:49,477
[ PAKU ]
YOU'VE ALWAYS LOVED
TAKING A BATH.

249
00:13:49,510 --> 00:13:51,510
[ KAMIKI ]
WELL, OF COURSE.
I AM A GIRL.

250
00:13:51,543 --> 00:13:54,943
[ LAUGHS ]
THREE GIRLS TAKING A BATH.
TOGETHER.

251
00:13:54,977 --> 00:13:57,843
WHAT DO YOU SAY, GUYS,
WE BUST ASS OVER THERE
AND HAVE OURSELVES A PEEK?

252
00:13:57,877 --> 00:14:00,677
HELLO? YOU'RE SUPPOSED
TO BE A MONK, SHIMA.

253
00:14:00,710 --> 00:14:02,977
YOU'RE GETTING BACK
INTO YOUR BAD HABITS AGAIN.

254
00:14:03,010 --> 00:14:06,877
AW, SHUT IT.
YOU GUYS ARE BOTH JUST
AS INTERESTED AS I AM.

255
00:14:06,910 --> 00:14:10,677
[ YUKIO ] EXCUSE ME.
YOUR TEACHER'S
SITTING RIGHT HERE.

256
00:14:12,643 --> 00:14:14,677
COME ON, LOOSEN UP
A LITTLE.

257
00:14:14,710 --> 00:14:17,977
YOU MIGHT BE OUR TEACHER,
BUT YOU'RE ALSO A FRESHMAN,
JUST LIKE US.

258
00:14:19,743 --> 00:14:23,043
IT'S MY POLICY NOT TO ENGAGE
IN FRIVOLOUS PURSUITS.

259
00:14:23,077 --> 00:14:24,777
UH.

260
00:14:24,810 --> 00:14:25,977
[ PAKU ]
THIS IS IT.

261
00:14:27,143 --> 00:14:29,510
WOW. THIS IS GREAT!

262
00:14:29,543 --> 00:14:31,877
I'VE NEVER TAKEN A BATH
WITH FRIENDS BEFORE.

263
00:14:31,910 --> 00:14:34,043
- OH, SORRY.
- HMM?

264
00:14:34,077 --> 00:14:35,710
COULD YOU WAIT OUT HERE?

265
00:14:35,743 --> 00:14:38,477
- WELL, CAN'T I COME IN?
- NO, YOU CAN'T.

266
00:14:38,510 --> 00:14:40,777
I'M SHY, AND I DON'T WANT YOU
TO SEE ME NAKED.

267
00:14:40,810 --> 00:14:44,243
HUH?
IF YOU WERE MY FRIEND,
YOU'D UNDERSTAND.

268
00:14:44,277 --> 00:14:46,010
OH, I KNOW.

269
00:14:46,043 --> 00:14:49,610
INSTEAD OF WAITING OUT HERE,
GO TO THE STORE
AND BUY ME SOME FRUIT MILK.

270
00:14:49,643 --> 00:14:52,043
I WANT TO DRINK IT
AFTER MY BATH.

271
00:14:52,077 --> 00:14:54,277
[ FOOTSTEPS RECEDING ]
MM-HMM.

272
00:14:54,310 --> 00:14:56,277
'KAY. THANKS.

273
00:15:00,043 --> 00:15:03,243
HEY, WHAT YOU DOING?

274
00:15:03,277 --> 00:15:07,810
OH, NOTHING.
JUST GOING TO GO GET
SOME FRUIT MILK.

275
00:15:07,843 --> 00:15:09,777
HEY!
[ GASPS ]

276
00:15:09,810 --> 00:15:11,910
LISTEN, STOP DOING THAT.

277
00:15:11,943 --> 00:15:15,177
DOING WHAT?
THAT! ACTING LIKE
HER ERRAND GIRL.

278
00:15:15,210 --> 00:15:16,943
STOP IT.

279
00:15:18,977 --> 00:15:22,610
I'M NOT HER ERRAND GIRL.
I'M JUST HELPING OUT
MY FRIEND.

280
00:15:22,643 --> 00:15:26,710
YOU BELIEVE THAT?
DO YOU HONESTLY THINK
THAT'S WHAT'S GOING ON?

281
00:15:26,743 --> 00:15:28,677
YOU KNOW YOU DON'T.

282
00:15:28,710 --> 00:15:32,377
I-- I'M TIRED
OF BEING THE ONE
WHO ALWAYS NEEDS HELP.

283
00:15:32,410 --> 00:15:35,177
ALWAYS HIDING BEHIND OTHERS.

284
00:15:35,210 --> 00:15:37,043
I JUST WANT TO--

285
00:15:37,077 --> 00:15:40,010
TO BE LIKE YOU AND YUKI.

286
00:15:40,043 --> 00:15:43,577
TO BE STRONG ENOUGH TO HELP
SOMEONE OUT FOR A CHANGE.

287
00:15:43,610 --> 00:15:46,910
SHE IS THE FIRST FRIEND
I'VE EVER HAD IN MY WHOLE LIFE.

288
00:15:46,943 --> 00:15:49,243
YOU DON'T GET IT
'CAUSE YOU'VE ALWAYS
BEEN STRONG.

289
00:15:49,277 --> 00:15:51,077
YOU'VE ALWAYS HAD FRIENDS.

290
00:15:51,110 --> 00:15:53,377
UH, HEY, HOLD UP.

291
00:15:54,210 --> 00:15:55,977
UH.

292
00:15:56,010 --> 00:15:57,277
[ SHOUTS ]

293
00:15:57,310 --> 00:16:00,677
THANK GOODNESS.
AT LEAST THE BATHTUB'S CLEAN.

294
00:16:00,710 --> 00:16:04,243
IT'S LIKE THE HAUNTED
MANSION IN HERE.
AM I RIGHT?

295
00:16:04,277 --> 00:16:06,477
HEY, IZUMO?
HMM?

296
00:16:06,510 --> 00:16:09,410
WHY ARE YOU BEING MEAN
TO HER?
HUH?

297
00:16:09,443 --> 00:16:11,477
WELL, WHAT DIFFERENCE
DOES IT MAKE?

298
00:16:11,510 --> 00:16:14,110
I MEAN, IT'S NOT LIKE SHE'S
REALLY MY FRIEND OR ANYTHING.

299
00:16:14,143 --> 00:16:17,577
IF SHE WANTS TO DO
WHATEVER I TELL HER TO,
HEY, THAT'S HER DEAL.

300
00:16:17,610 --> 00:16:19,577
OH, BUT YOU'RE DIFFERENT.

301
00:16:19,610 --> 00:16:21,777
YOU'RE MY BEST FRIEND
IN THE WHOLE WORLD.

302
00:16:21,810 --> 00:16:24,877
WHEN YOU DECIDED
TO COME TO THE CRAM SCHOOL,
I WAS SO HAPPY.

303
00:16:24,910 --> 00:16:27,343
WE'RE GONNA HAVE
SO MUCH FUN.

304
00:16:27,377 --> 00:16:29,943
BUT I'M BARELY KEEPING UP
ON ALL THE CLASSES AS IT IS.

305
00:16:29,977 --> 00:16:32,843
DON'T WORRY.
I PROMISE
I'LL LOOK AFTER YOU.

306
00:16:38,110 --> 00:16:39,477
DID YOU HEAR?

307
00:16:39,510 --> 00:16:43,010
KAMIKI FREAKED OUT AGAIN.
SHE SAYS SHE SAW A GHOST.

308
00:16:43,043 --> 00:16:44,743
SHE'S CREEPY.

309
00:16:44,777 --> 00:16:46,543
I BET
SHE'S LYING.

310
00:16:46,577 --> 00:16:49,310
SHE'S GOT NO FRIENDS
AND JUST WANTS ATTENTION.

311
00:16:49,343 --> 00:16:52,577
YEAH, SHE'S A LONER.
[ ALL GIGGLING ]

312
00:16:52,610 --> 00:16:56,310
WAIT UP, MISS KAMIKI.
I'M ON THE COMMITTEE TOO.
LET ME HELP YOU.

313
00:16:57,943 --> 00:17:01,410
IF YOU HANG AROUND ME,
MISS PAKU, THEY'RE JUST GONNA
MAKE FUN OF YOU TOO.

314
00:17:01,443 --> 00:17:03,343
HUH?
[ LAUGHS ]

315
00:17:03,377 --> 00:17:05,477
LIKE ANYONE CARES WHAT THEY SAY.

316
00:17:09,510 --> 00:17:11,610
I'M NOT VERY NICE.
JUST SAYIN'.

317
00:17:11,643 --> 00:17:14,110
[ GIGGLES ]

318
00:17:14,143 --> 00:17:17,343
ALL YOU HAVE TO DO, PAKU,
IS STICK WITH ME,
AND YOU'LL BE ALL RIGHT.

319
00:17:20,743 --> 00:17:23,177
LISTEN, IZUMO?
HMM?

320
00:17:23,210 --> 00:17:25,410
I THINK I SHOULD QUIT GOING
TO CRAM SCHOOL.

321
00:17:25,443 --> 00:17:29,243
WHAT?
I CAN'T KEEP UP
WITH THE CLASSES, AND--

322
00:17:29,277 --> 00:17:32,110
AND I CAN'T SEE MYSELF
RISKING MY LIFE IN BATTLE.

323
00:17:32,143 --> 00:17:34,610
BUT-- BUT I SAID I'D--

324
00:17:34,643 --> 00:17:37,443
HMM-MM. THAT DOESN'T MAKE
ANY SENSE.

325
00:17:37,477 --> 00:17:43,277
BESIDES, I DON'T LIKE HOW YOU
MAKE FUN OF THE PEOPLE IN CLASS
WHO TRY TO DO THEIR BEST.

326
00:17:43,310 --> 00:17:45,343
I'M SORRY.

327
00:17:45,377 --> 00:17:47,577
I'VE BEEN MEANING TO TELL YOU,
BUT I COULDN'T.

328
00:17:49,910 --> 00:17:53,143
THAT'S THE THING.
A REAL FRIEND WOULD'VE
TOLD YOU EARLIER.

329
00:17:53,177 --> 00:17:54,843
SORRY.

330
00:17:56,010 --> 00:17:57,277
HUH?

331
00:17:58,210 --> 00:18:00,177
[ BOTH SCREAM ]

332
00:18:00,210 --> 00:18:01,777
[ GASPS ]
HUH?

333
00:18:01,810 --> 00:18:04,277
THAT SOUNDS LIKE MISS KAMIKI
AND MISS PAKU.

334
00:18:04,310 --> 00:18:06,877
I GOT THIS.
GO TELL YUKIO.

335
00:18:08,643 --> 00:18:12,843
RIN'S SO AMAZING.
HE DIDN'T HESITATE.
HE JUST TOOK OFF.

336
00:18:12,877 --> 00:18:14,777
HOW CAN HE BE SO BRAVE?

337
00:18:14,810 --> 00:18:16,377
[ SCREAMING ]

338
00:18:16,410 --> 00:18:19,310
DON'T GO. DON'T LEAVE!
I WANNA GO TOO!

339
00:18:19,343 --> 00:18:21,310
- [ GRUNTS ]
- PAKU!

340
00:18:23,410 --> 00:18:26,143
A GHOUL'S TEMPTAINT
HAS TO BE TREATED RIGHT AWAY...

341
00:18:26,177 --> 00:18:27,810
OR ELSE--

342
00:18:27,843 --> 00:18:30,843
I HUMBLY APPEAL TO THEE,
OH, GODDESS INARI.

343
00:18:34,243 --> 00:18:37,710
GRANT MY REQUEST.
LEAVE NOT MY PRAYERS
TO THEE UNFULFILLED.

344
00:18:37,743 --> 00:18:39,577
[ SNARLS ]

345
00:18:41,477 --> 00:18:44,077
WHAT DO I DO?
I HAVE TO SAVE HER.

346
00:18:44,110 --> 00:18:47,843
PAKU'S THE ONLY FRIEND
I'VE GOT, AND I'M NOT GONNA
LET HER GET HURT.

347
00:18:47,877 --> 00:18:50,510
[ PAKU ]
HMM-MM. THAT DOESN'T MAKE
ANY SENSE.

348
00:18:50,543 --> 00:18:53,377
- [ GASPS ]
- <i>I DON'T LIKE IT--</i>

349
00:18:55,377 --> 00:18:59,577
HUH? HOW DARE YOU.
YOUR HEART IS WEAK.

350
00:18:59,610 --> 00:19:01,077
WHAT?

351
00:19:01,110 --> 00:19:03,910
YOU ARE NOT WORTHY
OF OUR HELP.

352
00:19:03,943 --> 00:19:08,077
- [ GASPS ]
- [ GRUNTING ]

353
00:19:08,110 --> 00:19:10,543
TEAR UP THE PAPER.
DO IT!

354
00:19:12,943 --> 00:19:14,210
GOOD.

355
00:19:14,243 --> 00:19:16,277
[ ROARS ]

356
00:19:17,810 --> 00:19:19,310
STAY BACK.
I GOT IT.

357
00:19:19,343 --> 00:19:21,743
DAMN IT.
WHAT SHOULD I DO?

358
00:19:21,777 --> 00:19:24,210
I CAN'T DRAW MY SWORD
IN FRONT OF HER.

359
00:19:24,243 --> 00:19:27,077
HURRY THE HELL UP, YUKIO.

360
00:19:27,110 --> 00:19:29,110
- [ SHIEMI ]
RIN!
- HEY!

361
00:19:29,143 --> 00:19:30,577
[ SHIEMI ]
PAKU!

362
00:19:30,610 --> 00:19:33,243
YOU KEEP THE GHOUL BUSY, RIN.
I'LL TAKE CARE OF MISS PAKU.

363
00:19:33,277 --> 00:19:36,043
- COME ON,
DON'T JUST STAND THERE.
- HUH?

364
00:19:36,077 --> 00:19:38,577
THAT'S EASIER SAID THAN DONE.

365
00:19:38,610 --> 00:19:40,610
[ SNARLING ]

366
00:19:43,110 --> 00:19:45,210
IT LOOKS A LOT
LIKE A BURN.

367
00:19:45,243 --> 00:19:47,277
[ KAMIKI ]
IT'S A GHOUL'S TEMPTAINT.

368
00:19:47,310 --> 00:19:49,110
IT'LL GO NECROTIC SOON.

369
00:19:49,143 --> 00:19:52,043
THEN THERE'S NO TIME
TO MOVE HER.
I HAVE TO DO SOMETHING NOW.

370
00:19:52,077 --> 00:19:55,010
MY YOUNG PRINCE.

371
00:19:55,043 --> 00:19:56,843
[ GASPS, YELLS ]

372
00:19:56,877 --> 00:19:59,277
[ SHOUTING ]

373
00:19:59,310 --> 00:20:01,177
RIN!
I'M OKAY.

374
00:20:01,210 --> 00:20:04,077
WHAT DO I DO?
WHAT DO I DO?

375
00:20:04,110 --> 00:20:06,710
TO TREAT A BURN
I'M GONNA NEED--

376
00:20:06,743 --> 00:20:08,610
MR. SANCHO!
HUH?

377
00:20:08,643 --> 00:20:10,977
WHERE AM I GONNA FIND SOME?

378
00:20:11,010 --> 00:20:12,343
NEE!

379
00:20:12,377 --> 00:20:15,010
- YEAH, NEE?
- [ GRUNTING ]

380
00:20:17,477 --> 00:20:20,577
OH! NICE JOB, NEE.
YOU BROUGHT ME SOME
MR. SANCHO.

381
00:20:20,610 --> 00:20:22,877
NO, THAT'S AN ALOE VERA PLANT.

382
00:20:22,910 --> 00:20:25,210
WAIT. WHY IS ALOE VERA
SPROUTING FROM YOUR FAMILIAR?

383
00:20:25,243 --> 00:20:26,910
[ ROARS ]

384
00:20:26,943 --> 00:20:28,610
[ GRUNTING ]

385
00:20:28,643 --> 00:20:30,143
FORGIVE ME.

386
00:20:30,177 --> 00:20:33,177
I ONLY DO...

387
00:20:33,210 --> 00:20:36,843
AS MY MASTER
COMMANDS ME TO.

388
00:20:36,877 --> 00:20:38,743
HE MEAN SATAN?

389
00:20:41,443 --> 00:20:46,010
NO USE.
I DON'T HAVE A CHANCE
AGAINST HIM LIKE THIS.

390
00:20:47,343 --> 00:20:49,510
CAN'T HOLD ON.

391
00:20:49,543 --> 00:20:52,277
- [ YUKIO ]
RIN!
- [ GUNFIRE ]

392
00:20:52,310 --> 00:20:55,010
- GET BACK HERE.
- [ GUNFIRE ]

393
00:20:57,010 --> 00:20:58,843
ARE YOU OKAY?
ARE YOU HURT?

394
00:20:58,877 --> 00:21:01,910
YOU'RE LATE!
BUT I STILL MADE IT,
DIDN'T I?

395
00:21:01,943 --> 00:21:04,777
SHIEMI, HOW'S MISS PAKU?

396
00:21:04,810 --> 00:21:07,043
OKAY, I THINK.

397
00:21:07,077 --> 00:21:09,577
NEE.
YOU DID GOOD.

398
00:21:09,610 --> 00:21:12,277
WHO KNOWS
WHAT MIGHT HAVE HAPPENED
IF YOU HADN'T BEEN HERE.

399
00:21:12,310 --> 00:21:14,577
[ BOTH GASP ]

400
00:21:18,977 --> 00:21:20,810
MISS PAKU!

401
00:21:20,843 --> 00:21:22,143
[ GROANS ]

402
00:21:22,177 --> 00:21:26,043
MISS MORIYAMA?
THANKS A LOT...

403
00:21:26,077 --> 00:21:28,410
FOR SAVING ME.

404
00:21:30,077 --> 00:21:31,610
UH-HUH.

405
00:21:31,643 --> 00:21:33,977
[ CRYING ]

406
00:21:34,010 --> 00:21:37,043
HMM?
HEY, ARE YOU OKAY?

407
00:21:37,077 --> 00:21:39,377
DON'T LOOK AT ME!

408
00:21:39,410 --> 00:21:41,643
I'M SO ASHAMED.

409
00:21:41,677 --> 00:21:45,110
I DON'T WANT ANYONE
SEEING ME LIKE THIS.

410
00:21:45,143 --> 00:21:47,343
I COULDN'T DO ANYTHING.

411
00:21:47,377 --> 00:21:51,343
I COULDN'T EVEN HELP
THE ONLY FRIEND I EVER HAD.

412
00:21:51,377 --> 00:21:53,610
AND NOW SHE HATES ME.

413
00:21:57,043 --> 00:21:58,910
JUST PUT IT ON
AND GET GOING.

414
00:21:58,943 --> 00:22:01,743
[ FOOTSTEPS RECEDING ]

415
00:22:04,877 --> 00:22:07,377
[ GROWLING ]

416
00:22:08,777 --> 00:22:10,543
SO YOU FAILED.

417
00:22:10,577 --> 00:22:13,310
[ GROWLS ]
WAS THAT A HOWL?

418
00:22:13,343 --> 00:22:18,710
OR PERHAPS YOU'RE AMUSED
AT HOW FAR I'VE FALLEN
TO BECOME A DEMON'S LAPDOG.

419
00:22:21,743 --> 00:22:24,743
♪ [ MAN SINGING IN JAPANESE ]

420
00:23:51,510 --> 00:23:55,410
WOULD YOU MIND EXPLAINING
WHY YOU'RE NAKED?

421
00:23:55,443 --> 00:23:57,710
IT JUST HAPPENED?

422
00:23:57,743 --> 00:24:00,443
NEVER MIND.
JUST GET EVERYONE
OUT OF HERE.

423
00:24:03,543 --> 00:24:06,643
[ KAMIKI ]
I'D RATHER DIE THAN BE FRIENDS
WITH THESE LOSERS.

424
00:24:06,677 --> 00:24:09,210
[ SUGURO ]
WITH A PERSONALITY LIKE THAT,
NO WONDER YOU'RE ALL ALONE.

425
00:24:09,243 --> 00:24:11,177
[ YUKIO ]
YOU NEED TO LEARN TO GET ALONG.

426
00:24:11,210 --> 00:24:13,743
EXORCISTS DO NOT GO
INTO BATTLE ALONE.

